related_items.title: Athens, Egypt, Rhine, Switzerland, Tyrol, Salzburg
description: 1 album (254 albumen prints) ; 40.5 x 51 cm. (album) | Scenic views of archaeological sites, antiquities, mountains, rivers, historic buildings, monuments, and cities in Austria, Egypt, Germany, Greece, and Switzerland. A large number of photographs depict mountains, glaciers and passes in the Alps, including Chamonix-Mont Blanc, Finsteraarhorn, Jungfrau and Matterhorn, the Grindelwald Glacier, the Mythen Mountains and the Brenner Pass. Subjects include villages; tourist camps and hostels; health resorts; passes; mountain railroads; waterfalls; bridges; forts and fortifications; monuments and memorials; castles and palaces; temples; and ruins. The cities represented in Switzerland include Bad Pfäfers; Bad Ragaz; Bern; Brunnen; Engelberg; Fribourg; Geneva; Interlaken; Lucern; Pontresina; Zermatt; and Zurich; in Germany, Berchtesgaden and Cologne; in Austria, Badgastein, Salzburg, and Innsbruck; in Greece, Athens and Pireaus. The archaeological sites and antiquities depicted in Greece include the Acropolis; Parthenon; Temple of Athena Nike; the monument of Philopappus; Hephaisteion; in Egypt, the Temple of Hathor; Ramesseum; Gerf Hussein; Great Temple at Abu Sunbul; the pyramids; and the ruins at Karnak, Dendara, Philae, and Thebes. Also includes images of Ephesus, Turkey.

related_items.title: The flying statesmen
description: 1 drawing : crayon, ink brush, and opaque white ; 48.6 x 38.5 cm. (sheet) | World War II editorial cartoon shows a battered man with a globe head rejoicing as four men (labeled "F.D.R., Churchill, Stalin, [and] Chiang") fly over on a flying carpet.  In 1943, Roosevelt and Churchill met Chinese leader Chiang Kai Shek for the first time in Cairo to plan strategy.  Roosevelt and Churchill then flew on to Teheran for another historic first meeting with Soviet leader Joseph Stalin.  Duffy views this as an encouraging event for the Allies.
